Create Vue components with stories and documentation. Follow existing patterns and templates.

## Templates
- Component: [AppTemplate.vue](mdc:packages/vue/src/components/template/AppTemplate.vue)
- Story: [AppTemplate.story.vue](mdc:packages/vue/src/components/template/AppTemplate.story.vue)
- Exports: [index.ts](mdc:packages/vue/src/components/template/index.ts)
- Documentation: [vue-component-story-documentation.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/vue-component-story-documentation.mdc)
- Code Standards: [frontend-code-structure.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/frontend-code-structure.mdc)

## Requirements
- Application-independent (no API dependencies)
- Create `.story.vue` and `.story.md` files
- Reference existing documentation instead of duplicating
- Follow patterns from `packages/vue/src/components` and analyze the existing folder structure
- Assign each component to a semantically appropriate directory
- If no suitable directory exists, create a new folder that reflects the component's purpose and scope
- Prioritize maintainability and logical grouping
